                        Scribe ʿAśratä Māryām. S. Additio
                           1.<date>Mid-19th cent.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ይካ(፡) for ይበል፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>ይዲ(፡) for ይበል፡ ዲያቆን፡</item>
                           <item>ይሕ(፡) for ይበል፡ ሕዝብ፡</item>
                           <item>በእ(ን)፡ for በእንተ፡</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ጸሎ፡</abbr> for <expan>ጸሎተ፡ </expan> (s. <locus target="#78vb">78vb</locus>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ኃዳፌ፡</abbr> for <expan>ኃዳፌ፡ ነፍስ፡ </expan> (s. <locus target="#80rb">80rb</locus>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ና፡ ከ(መ)፡ እ፡</abbr> for <expan>ናስተበቍዕ፡ ከመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ </expan> (s.
                                 <locus target="#10vb">10vb</locus>)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the Patriarch and
                           Metropolitan; names of the donor, her relatives and the commissioner of
                           the Ms. (in supplication formulas); incipits and headings of the texts;
                           directives for the ministers; some of the musical notation signs above
                           the lines; most of the abbreviations; elements of the punctuation signs
                           and Ethiopic numerals.
 
 The text in fols. 26r, 32r and the
                           incipits of most Anaphoras are written alternately with red and black
                           lines.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
